  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "You are given a string S containing uppercase English letters (A–Z).\n\nInterpret the string as an Excel-style column label and convert it into the corresponding column number.\n\nMapping:\nA = 1  \nB = 2  \n…  \nZ = 26\n\nAA = 27  \nAB = 28  \nAZ = 52  \nBA = 53  \n…\n\nYour task:\n\nConvert the given string into its numeric value.\n\nThis works exactly like converting from base-26, where:\n\ndigits are A=1 to Z=26\nstring is left→right (“ABC” like a number in base-26)\n\n✔ Example\n\nInput:\n\nAB\n\n\nOutput:\n\n28\n\n\nExplanation:\n\nA = 1 → (1 × 26)\nB = 2 → (2)\n\nTotal = 26 + 2 = 28",
